validate

public void validate(javax.faces.context.FacesContext context)
Description copied from class: netgest.bo.xwc.framework.components.XUIInput

Perform the following algorithm to validate the local value of this XUIInput.

  • Retrieve the submitted value with getSubmittedValue(). If this returns null, exit without further processing. (This indicates that no value was submitted for this component.)

  • Convert the submitted value into a "local value" of the appropriate data type by calling XUIInput.getConvertedValue(javax.faces.context.FacesContext, java.lang.Object).

  • Validate the property by calling XUIInput.validateValue(javax.faces.context.FacesContext, java.lang.Object).

  • If the valid property of this component is still true, retrieve the previous value of the component (with getValue()), store the new local value using setValue(), and reset the submitted value to null. If the local value is different from the previous value of this component, fire a ValueChangeEvent to be broadcast to all interested listeners.

Application components implementing XUIInput that wish to perform validation with logic embedded in the component should perform their own correctness checks, and then call the super.validate() method to perform the standard processing described above.
